<P>The light now enabled him to take
a more accurate &s;urvey of the place.
He perceived that &s;ome few &s;tones of
the &s;teps which had fallen, &s;till remain|ed
attached to the wall, but he feared
to trust to their &s;upport only. He  ob|&s;erved,
however, that <GAP DESC="illegible" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" EXTENT="1 word"> it&s;elf
was partly decayed, and con&s;equently
rugged with the corners of hal<GAP DESC="illegible" EXTENT="1 letter"> worn
&s;tones. On the&s;e &s;mall projections he
