of the woods. One evening &s;he took
her lute to a favourite &s;pot on the &s;ea
&s;hore, and re&s;igning her&s;elf to a plea&s;ing
&s;adne&s;s, touched &s;ome &s;weet and plain|tive
airs. The purple flu&s;h of evening
