&s;oon &s;ub&s;ide. At length, however,
the delightful con&s;ciou&s;ne&s;s of Vereza's
love bore her high above every other
&s;en&s;ation; again the &s;cene more brightly
glowed, and again her fancy overcame
the po&s;&s;ibility of evil.</P>
<P>During the evening, a tender and
timid re&s;pect di&s;tingui&s;hed the behavi|our
of the count towards Julia, who,
